    "(35)Proof: By construction of the gluing map gl and Theorem B.4 we have gl•(π C ⊗ π C ′) = π D = π D • B D.To finish the proof it therefore suffices to verify that normalization factors relating the σ's to the π's depending on boundary conditions agree.For ϕ ∈ H b C 1 and ϕ ′ ∈ H b ′ C ′ 1 we find σ C (ϕ) = D -|F C | d 1/4 b π C (ϕ), σ C ′ (ϕ ′) = D -|F C ′ | d 1/4 b ′ π C ′ (ϕ),and We further define S ⋆ C to be the set of states ω ∈ S C for which ω = ω • Ad[t(u)] for all unitaries u ∈ Tube S.(σ D • B D)(ϕ ⊗ ϕ ′) = δ b I,b ′ I ′ D -|F D | d b d b ′ d 2 b I 1/4 (π D • B D)(ϕ ⊗ ϕ ′).For any X ∈ Irr Z(C) we let S ⋆ X C = S ⋆ C ∩ S P X C. We say that ω ∈ S ⋆ X C satisfies maximally mixed boundary conditions of type X.",
